extract_class_signature(clazz)  Given a class, return the signature string of function  class.__init__ .  Arguments   clazz :  class object .   Returns  str . A string signature of function  class.__init__ .  Examples  # mod.py
import sophon

class foo(object):
    def __init__(self):
        pass

class bar(object):
    def __init__(self, a, b='b', c=None, **kwargs):
        pass

print extract_class_signature(foo)
# print  mod.foo()  to the console

print extract_class_signature(bar)
# print  mod.bar(a, b='b', c=None, **kwargs)  to the console   [source]
